  "title": "IT Project Engineer (Central)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Support project delivery by completing project milestones and deliverables</li><li>Perform hardware and software installations for turnkey solutions</li><li>Prepare and execute Statements of Work (SOW)</li><li>Coordinate with external parties and customers for problem resolution</li><li>Participate in System Acceptance Testing (SAT) with vendors and customers</li><li>Troubleshoot and debug issues as they arise</li><li>Develop and maintain technical and configuration documentation</li><li>Document and explain network topologies, diagrams, and system layouts</li><li>Prepare standard documentation, including SOW, system handover documents, and inventory lists</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in IT, Computer Engineering, or related discipline</li><li><strong>Operating Systems:</strong> Linux – CentOS, SUSE</li><li><strong>Networking:</strong> Dell, Cisco</li><li><strong>Firewall:</strong> Fortinet</li><li><strong>Big Data Technologies:</strong> Hadoop (HDFS, ZooKeeper), Cloudera, Hue, Apache, Elasticsearch</li><li>Knowledge of Fiber-Optic transmission devices</li><li>Virtualization technologies is an added advantage</li></ul><p><strong>Work Location:</strong> Central (Novena)<br /></p><p>(EA Reg No: 20C0312)<br />Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>qianyu@talentsis.com.sg</strong> for immediate processing.<br />Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
